medical_history.chief_complaint: Headache, dizziness, balance problems, fatigue, irritability, and difficulties with sleep and concentration after head trauma.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 11 days prior to evaluation after being struck in the head during a sailboat race. Initially, she was dazed, confused, and experienced a loss of consciousness for several minutes. Symptoms included occasional frontotemporal headaches rated 3/10 in severity, dizziness, balance problems, fatigue, and difficulty concentrating. Activity reportedly alleviated some symptoms.
medical_history.past_medical_history: History of several sports-related injuries, including a concussion at age 13 without loss of consciousness, leading to dizziness for several days and headaches for 3 months.
